shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...form a black 7x7 grid. You are required to duplicate the pattern of the input grid onto the output grid. However, the number of duplicates on the output grid is calculated by the number of colored pixels on the input grid. And the exact place of the copied pattern on the output grid also follows the spot of each of the colored squares on the input grid.

You have to paste the pattern of the input grid onto the output grid. However, the numeral of duplicates on the output grid is dependent on the number of colored pixels on the input grid. And the location of the copied pattern on the output grid also follows the location of every one of the colored squares on the input grid.

However, the number of copies on the output grid is given by the amount of colored pixels on the input grid. Also, the place of the copied pattern on the output grid mimics the place of each of the colored rectangles on the input grid.

Then, for each colored square in the output, do the following: add a light green square 1 above and to the left, 1 above and to the right, 1 below and to the left, 1 below and to the right.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...make the grid smaller than the shape and the colors are completely different from the shape.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...make the grid larger than the shape and the two colors are not like in shape at all.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...change the grid size and use different colors from the shape.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...imagine the original pattern is a 9x9 grid. What you need to do is copy the pattern in the 9x9 to the 3x3 grid. So you have 3 3x3 grid inside of the bigger grid(Top left, top middle, top right, middle left, middle, middle right, bottom left, bottom middle, bottom right). For example if the input pattern is a l shape you would only copy this to the top left, left and bottom left grid.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...understand the original pattern is a 3x3 grid. What you need to do is translate the pattern in the 3x3 to the 9x9 grid. As a result, you have 9 3x3 grid around the bigger grid(Top left, top middle, top right, middle left, middle, middle right, bottom left, bottom middle, bottom right). For instance if the input pattern is a square shape you would only translate this to the top middle, central and bottom middle grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...consider the original pattern is a 3x3 grid. What you need to do is mirror the pattern in the 3x3 to the 9x9 grid. Instead, you have 9 3x3 grid outside of the bigger grid(Top left, top middle, top right, middle left, middle, middle right, bottom left, bottom middle, bottom right). For instance if the input pattern is a l shape you would only mirror this to the top right, right and bottom right grid.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...visualize the original pattern is a 3x3 grid. What you need to do is rotate the pattern In the 3x3 to the 9x9 grid. Therefore, you have 9 3x3 grid underneath of the bigger grid(Top left, top middle, top right, middle left, middle, middle right, bottom left, bottom middle, bottom right). For example if the input pattern is a l shape you would only rotate this to the top middle, center and bottom middle grid.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...imagine the original pattern is a 3x3 grid. What you need to do is copy the pattern in the 3x3 to the 9x9 grid. So you have 9 3x3 grid inside of the bigger grid(Top left, top middle, top right, middle left, middle, middle right, bottom left, bottom middle, bottom right). For example if the input pattern is a l shape you would only copy this to the top middle, middle and bottom middle grid.

shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...add more same color grids to the group.

shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...surround pink with green color, yellow with light blue and red with blue.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...make the output repeat the pattern horizontally from the bottom of the grid by the number of the colored grid on the background using the unique background explained above.

shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...only copy the size and position of the solid rectangular block, except other single colored pixels.

shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...only copy the size and color of the solid rectangular block, except other single colored pixels.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...keep the same color and rotate the pattern to create a 9x9 grid. Each tile in the input grid is a 3x3 grid pattern on the output.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...keep the same color and pattern but increase to a 30x30 grid. Each tile in the input grid is a 10x10 grid pattern on the output.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...keep same color and pattern but increase to a 9x9 grid. Each tile in the input grid is a 3x3 grid pattern on the output.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...replicate the input grid. Then, using the color of the colored ellipse, make the smallest rectangle possible that will fit inside the four pink dots. The outside of the new ellipse should touch the inside of all four pink dots.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid. Then, using the color of the colored rectangle, make the largest rectangle possible that will fit inside the four grey dots. The outside of the new rectangle should touch the inside of all four grey dots.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid. Then, using the color of the colored polygon, make the largest rectangle possible that will fit inside the four light blue dots. The outside of the new rectangle should touch the inside of all four light blue dots.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...immitate the input grid. Then, using the color of the colored circle, make the largest square possible that will fit inside the four black dots. The outside of the new circle should contact the inside of all four black dots.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...clone the input grid. Then, using the color of the colored square, make the largest possible rectangle that will fit inside the four brown dots. The outside of the new square should be outside all four brown dots.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...change the input grid. Then, you will remove 2 4x4 blocks from the grid, each touching the corner of the 4x4 colored square in the input. The color of each 4x4 block should be the different color from the same corner of the 4x4 colored square. If the 4x4 colored square is not in the center of the input, all of the 4x4 blocks you are removing will be missing.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid. Then, you will add 4 2x2 blocks to the grid, each touching the corner of the 2x2 colored square in the input. The color of each 2x2 block should be the same color as the opposite corner of the 2x2 colored square. If the 2x2 colored square is not in the center of the input, some of the 2x2 blocks you are adding may be off the page.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...alter the input grid. Then, you will add 3 3x3 blocks to the grid, each touching the corner of the 3x3 colored square in the input. The color of each 3x3 block should be the same color as the adjacent corner of the 3x3 colored square. If the 3x3 colored square is not in the center of the input, some of the 3x3 blocks you are adding may be outside off the page.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...duplicate the input grid. Then, you will add 5 1x1 blocks to the grid, each touching the corner of the 1x1 colored square in the input. The color of each 1x1 block should be the same color as the neighboring corner of the 1x1 colored square. If the 1x1 colored square is not in the center of the input, some of the 1x1 blocks you are adding may be out of reach.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid. Then, you will remove 4 2x2 blocks from the grid, each touching the corner of the 2x2 colored square in the input. The color of each 2x2 block should be the same color as the adjacent corner of the 2x2 colored square. If the 2x2 colored square is not in the center of the input, some of the 2x2 blocks you are removing may be off the page.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...fill the left-upper black area with green; the middle with yellow; and the blue in the right-down.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...fill the left-upper black area with red; the middle with blue; and the pink in the right-down.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...fill the left-upper black area with yellow; the middle with green; and the red in the right-down.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...fill the right-upper black area with blue; the middle with red; and the green in the right-down.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...fill the left-upper black area with blue; the middle with red; and the green in the right-down.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...overlay the top 4x4 grid of green pixels over the bottom 4x4 grid of brown pixels or vice versa.After you complete the overlay whichever pixels are still black will be changed to red in the output. All the other pixels which are green, brown, or both will be changed to black.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...overlay the top 5x5 grid of green pixels with the bottom 5x5 grid of yellow pixels or vice versa.After you complete the overlay whichever pixels are still black will be changed to red in the output. All the other pixels which are green, yellow, or both will be changed to black.

All the other pixels which are black, blue, or both will be changed to gray.

All the other pixels which are green, blue, or both will be changed to black
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...overlay the top 3x3 grid of green pixels over the bottom 3x3 grid of blue pixels or vice versa.After you complete the overlay whichever pixels are still black will be changed to pink in the output. All the other pixels which are green, blue, or both will be changed to black.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...delete the input grid for the output workspace. Reorder each of the interior corner colored pixels to the exterior corner similar to their input position. Meaning, place the lower right interior pixel such that its corner is touching the upper left corner of the upper left corner pixel of the monochromatic rectangle or square. You're placing pixel at a 45-degree angle to the exterior similar corner, do that with each interior corner square to create the incorrect output grid.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid to the output workspace. Move each of the exterior corner colored pixels to the interior corner opposite of their input position. Meaning, move the upper left exterior pixel such that its corner is touching the lower left corner of the lower left corner pixel of the monochromatic rectangle or square. You're moving pixel at a 45 degree angle to the interior opposite corner, do that with each exterior corner square to create the correct output grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid to the output workspace. Move each of the interior corner colored pixels to the exterior corner opposite of their input position. Meaning, move the upper left interior pixel such that its corner is touching the lower left corner of the lower left corner pixel of the monochromatic rectangle or square. You're moving pixel at a 45 degree angle to the exterior opposite corner, do that with each interior corner square to create the correct output grid.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid to the output workspace. Move each of the exterior corner colored pixels to the interior corner identical to their input position. Meaning, move the lower left exterior pixel such that its corner is touching the lower right corner of the lower right corner pixel of the monochromatic rectangle or square. You're moving pixel at a 45 degree angle to the interior identical corner, do that with each exterior corner square to create the incorrect output grid.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...copy the output grid to the input workspace. Move each of the interior corner colored pixels to the exterior corner opposite of their output position. Meaning, move the lower right interior pixel such that its corner is touching the upper right corner of the upper right corner pixel of the monochromatic rectangle or square. You're moving pixel at a 45 degree angle to the exterior opposite corner, do that with each interior corner square to create the correct input grid.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...keep the color with the most squares and everything else should be gray.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...make the color with the most squares gray and everything else should be gray.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...color the squares randomly, keeping the most squares as grey.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...keep the color with the most squares and everything else should be colored randomly.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...keep the color with the least squares and everything else should be green.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...place each color diagonally, alternating as follows: Blue and Red on the top half, Green and Yellow on the bottom half. The end result should almost resemble a diamond, with a gray center and four colored facets.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...form a circle in the middle with the following sequence of squares: Blue at the north pole, Red at the east pole, Green at the south pole, and Yellow at the west pole. This should make an abstract globe, with a gray center and four colored quadrants.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...create a cross in the center with Blue at the top, Red at the bottom, Green at the left, and Yellow at the right. This should create a type of compass rose, with a gray center and four directional arms.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...surround each square with the following, connected diagonally to each of the corners: Blue on the top left, Red on the top right, Green on the bottom left, Yellow on the bottom right. The end result should almost resemble a flower, with a gray center and four colored petals.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...put each square into the following pattern: Blue at the top, Red at the bottom, Green on the left, and Yellow on the right. The end result should vaguely resemble a window, with a gray center and four colored panes.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...repeat the same pattern of colors in the output pixels to the grid created in the input in the same position.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...repeat a varied pattern of colors in the input pixels to the grid created in the output in the same position.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...repeat the same pattern of colors in the input pixels to the circle created in the output in the same position.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...repeat the same pattern of colors in the input pixels to the grid created in the output in the same position.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...repeat the same pattern of colors in the input pixels to the grid created in the output in a different position.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid. Then, below the first colored block, place a gray block. After the gray block, continue down and place a block of the original color. Continue the pattern of original color followed by gray until you reach the bottom. Do this with each original colored block.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid. Then, to the right of the first colored block, place a red block. After the red block, continue to the right and place a block of the original color. Continue the pattern of original color followed by red until you reach the right side. Do this with each original colored block.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid. Then, to the right of the first colored block, place a gray block. After the gray block, continue to the right and place a block of the original color. Continue the pattern of original color followed by gray until you reach the right side. Do this with each original colored block.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid. Then, to the right of the first colored block, place a brown block. After the brown block, continue to the right and place a block of the original color. Continue the pattern of original color followed by brown until you reach the right side. Do this with each original colored block.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid. Then, to the left of the first colored block, place a gray block. After the gray block, continue to the left and place a block of the original color. Continue the pattern of original color followed by gray until you reach the left side. Do this with each original colored block.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...fit the red blocks in the small grid blocks where they go on the large red grid with the colored blocks as well.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...fit the yellow blocks in the small grid blocks where they go on the large red grid with the colored blocks as well.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...fit the blue blocks in the small grid blocks where they go on the large red grid with the colored blocks as well.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...fit the green blocks in the small grid blocks where they go on the large red grid with the colored blocks as well.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...fit the red blocks in the larger grid blocks where they go on the small red grid with the colored blocks as well.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...remove the colored squares that create a floor to the other pattern. you bring the patterns together by moving the pattern that is the same color as the line you remove.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...replace the colored squares that create a floor to the other pattern. you bring the patterns together by moving the pattern that is the same color as the circle you remove.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...remove the colored squares that create a roof to the other pattern. You bring the patterns together by moving the pattern that is a different color as the line you remove.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...construct the colored squares that keep apart the other patterns. You keep apart the patterns by shifting the pattern that is a different color as the line you add.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...add the colored squares that create a floor to the other pattern. You keep apart the patterns by shifting the pattern that is the same color as the line you add.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...make three rows of two different solid colors corresponding to the grey 4x4 blocks. The first 4x4 block is the color of the top row, and so on. Grey 4x4 with a 2x2 black box in the middle = light blue. Grey 4x4 with black = red. Grey 4x4 with black box center bottom = yellow. Grey 4x4 with no 1x2 black lines on the left and right = green. If there are any more, they are a different color.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...make three rows of three different solid colors corresponding to the grey 4x4 blocks. The first 4x4 block is the color of the top row, and so on.Grey 4x4 with a 2x2 black box in the middle = light blueGrey 4x4 with no black = redGrey 4x4 with black box center bottom = yellowGrey 4x4 with two 1x2 black lines on the left and right = greenIf there are any more, they are a different color.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...make three rows of three different solid colors not corresponding to the grey 4x4 blocks. The first 4x4 block is the color of the bottom row, and so on. Grey 4x4 with a 2x2 black box in the middle = red. Grey 4x4 with black = blue. Grey 4x4 with no black box center top = yellow. Grey 4x4 with two 1x2 black lines on the right and left = green. If there are any more, they are a different color.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...make four rows of three different solid colors corresponding to the grey 4x4 blocks. The first 4x4 block is the color of the top row, and so on. Grey 4x4 with a 2x2 black box in the middle = brown. Grey 4x4 with no black = pink. Grey 4x4 with black box center top = yellow. Grey 4x4 with two 1x2 black lines on the bottom and top = green. If there are any more, they are a different color.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...make three columns of three different solid colors corresponding to the grey 4x4 blocks. The first 4x4 block is the color of the left row, and so on. Grey 4x4 with a 2x2 black box in the center = pink. Grey 4x4 with no black = brown. Grey 4x4 with black box center top = blue. Grey 4x4 with two 1x2 black lines on the bottom and top = green. If there are any more, they are a different color.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...compare the squares in the top and bottom 4x4 square. If they match (both black or both color) make the output square black. If they do not match, make the output square green.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...compare the squares in the left and right 4x4 square. If they match (both black or both color) make the output square brown. If they do not match, make the output square light blue.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...compare the squares in the top and bottom 5x5 square. If they match (both green or both black) make the output square yellow. If they do not match, make the output square black.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...compare the squares in the top and bottom 3x3 square. If they match (both color or both brown) make the output square red. If they do not match, make the output square green.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...compare the squares in the left and right 3x3 square. If they match (both color or both black) make the output square gray. If they do not match, make the output square pink.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...extend the colored block horizontally until the right edge, then extend the block downward until the block meets the bottom edge or other colored block.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...extend the colorless block vertically until the top edge, then extend the block rightward until the block meets the right edge or another colorless block.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...reduce the colored block horizontally until the left edge, then shrink the block upward until the block meets the bottom edge or other colored block.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...shorten the colored block horizontally until the left edge, then shorten the block upward until the block meets the top edge or other colored block.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...extend the colored block vertically until the right edge, then extend the block downward until the block meets the left edge or other colored block.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...copy the colored object and copy the light blue object inside the colored object. Then leave the middle light blue blocks adjacent to the colored outlines in light blue.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...copy the colored object and copy the light blue object inside the colored object. Then change the middle light blue blocks adjacent to the colored outlines to the same color.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...copy the colored object without the light blue object inside the colored object. Then change the middle light blue blocks adjacent to the colored outlines to the same color.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...copy the colored object and copy the green object inside the colored object. Then change the middle light blue blocks adjacent to the colored outlines to the same color.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...do not copy the colored object but only the light blue object inside the colored object. Then change the middle light blue blocks adjacent to the colored outlines to the same color.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...rotate the shapes to become lines, hanging from the left of the new grid. The shapes will be arranged by width, narrowest starting at the top and widest at the bottom. The narrowest shape should start at the top right and extend all the way to the left to fill the grid. The next narrowest shape will fill in next to it and extend right the number of blocks of the original shape. The next widest shape will go next and extend right the number of blocks of the original shape. Do this until all shapes fill the grid horizontally. The empty space extending beside the straightened shapes (now lines) in the top-left of the grid will be gray.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...crumple the shapes to become lines, hanging from the top of the new grid. The shapes will be arranged by volume, smallest starting at the left and largest at the right. The smallest shape should start at the top right and extend partway down to fill the grid. The next smallest shape will fill in next to it and extend up the number of blocks of the original shape. The next largest shape will go next and extend up the number of blocks of the original shape. Do this until all shapes fill the grid vertically. The empty space extending below the straightened shapes (now lines) in the bottom-left of the grid will be red.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...bend the shapes to become lines, hanging from the bottom of the new grid. The shapes will be arranged by length, shortest starting at the right and longest at the left. The smallest shape should start at the top left and not extend all the way down to fill the grid. The next smallest shape will fill in next to it and extend up the number of blocks of the original shape. The next largest shape will go next and extend up the number of blocks of the original shape. Do this until all shapes fill the grid vertically. The empty space extending above the straightened shapes (now lines) in the bottom-right of the grid will be white.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...warp the shapes to become lines, hanging from the right of the new grid. The shapes will be arranged by their area, largest starting at the right and smallest at the left. The largest shape should start at the bottom left and extend all the way up to fill the grid. The next biggest shape will fill in next to it and extend down the number of blocks of the original shape. The next small shape will go next extend down the number of blocks of the original shape. Do this until all shapes fill the grid horizontally. The empty space extending below the straightened shapes (now lines) in the top-right of the grid will be green.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...straighten out the shapes to become lines, hanging from the top of the new grid. The shapes will be arranged by length, longest starting at the left and shortest at the right. The largest shape should start at the top left and extend all the way down to fill the grid. The next biggest shape will fill in next to it and extend down the number of blocks of the original shape. The next smallest shape will go next extend down the number of blocks of the original shape. Do this until all shapes fill the grid horizontally. The empty space extending below the straightened shapes (now lines) in the bottom-right of the grid will be black.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...take the secondary color and create a border frame from the location it is in. Take the color next to it and place it at the starting point of the border frame. The color box that is nearer should then be copied into 4 directions ensuring they are mirror images. A white box should be between each color box.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...take the main color and create a border frame from the location it is in. take the color next to it and put it on the end point of the border frame. take the color box that is further away and copy that into the 4 directions making sure they are mirror images. A black box should be between each color box.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...take the main color and remove the border frame from the location it is in. Take the color adjacent to it and dismiss it at the end point of the border frame. The color box that is closer should be copied into 3 directions making sure they are not mirror images. A black box can be ignored among each color box.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...discard the main color and create a border frame from the location it is in. shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...place a green square to the space left of any blue square, a yellow square in the space above any blue square, a brown square to the space on the right of any blue square and a black square to the space below any blue square.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...place a orange square to the space left of any black square, a red square in the space above any pink square, a purple square to the space on the right of any yellow square and a light blue square to the space below any green square.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...initiate from the right-most column and substitute the brown pixels in the odd-numbered columns with green.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...start from the right-most column and substitute the green pixels in the even-numbered columns with grey.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...begin from the right-most column and change the grey pixels in the odd-numbered columns with green.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...begin from the left-most column and replace the grey pixels in the odd-numbered columns with green.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...start from the topmost row and replace the grey pixels in the odd-numbered rows with green.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...fill the same color of any rectangle that is diagonal to the corner of the green square.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...fill the different color of any square that is vertical or horizontal to the corner of the green hexagon.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...fill the same color of any square that is vertical or horizontal to the corner of the brown square.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...fill the same color of any square that is vertical or horizontal to the corner of the green square.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...empty the same color of any square that is vertical or horizontal to the corner of the blue square.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...make a 3x3 grid. If the input grid has blue shapes, the output should be light grey with black in the four corners (making a grey plus sign). If the input grid has red shapes, the output should be light grey with black on the lower left, middle left, middle right and lower right (making a grey T shape). If the input grid has green shapes, the output should be light grey with black in the upper left, middle left, upper center and middle center (making a 2x2 black square in the upper left).
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...form a 3x3 triangle. If the input grid has blue shapes, the output should be dark blue with black in the four corners (making a blue plus sign). If the input grid has red shapes, the output should be dark blue with black on the bottom, middle and top (making a blue I shape). If the input grid has brown shapes, the output should be light grey with black in the upper left, middle left, middle center and lower center (forming a 2x2 black square in the middle).
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...make a 3x3 grid. If the input grid has black shapes, the output should be light grey with blue in the four corners (making a grey X sign). If the input grid has red shapes, the output should be light grey with black on the lower right, upper right, middle left and middle right (making a grey cross shape). If the input grid has green shapes, the output should be light grey with black in the lower left, middle left, lower center and middle center (creating a 2x2 black square in the lower left).
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...create a 2x2 square. If the input grid has blue shapes, the output should be light grey with green in the four corners (making a grey plus sign). If the input grid has red shapes, the output should be light grey with black on the upper left, middle left, middle right and upper right (making a grey H shape). If the input grid has yellow shapes, the output should be light grey with black in the lower left, middle left, upper center and middle center (making a 2x2 black square in the lower left).
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...design a 4x4 grid. If the input grid has pink shapes, the output should be light grey with black in the bottom corners (making a grey V sign). If the input grid has red shapes, the output should be light grey with black on the lower left, upper left, higher right and upper right (making a inverted T shape). If the input grid has green shapes, the output should be dark grey with black in the upper right, middle right, upper center and middle center (making a 2x2 black square in the upper right).

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...draw an up line with blue to which the green grid's row meet. and continue the green grid to the side of the yellow grid.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...draw an up line with brown to which the pink grid's row meet. and continue the brown grid to the side of the green grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...draw a down line with pink to which the red grid's row meet. and continue the pink grid to the side of the green grid.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...draw a down line with yellow to which the red grid's row meet. and continue the yellow grid to the side of the red grid.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...draw a down line with gray to which the black grid's row meet. and continue the gray grid to the side of the brown grid.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...fill the gray with light blue then extend a line out the empty spot to the the end of the grid.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...fill the gray with yellow then shorten a line into the filled spot to the the start of the grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...fill the gray with red then extend a line out the full area to the end of the grid.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...fill the gray with brown then extend a line out the empty spot to the top end of the grid.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...fill the green with pink then extend a line out the empty spot to the side end of the grid.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...change all green squares to light blue and all light blue squares to green. Everything else keep the same as input.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...change all gray squares to yellow and all light blue squares to gray. Everything else keep the same as input.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...change all gray squares to light blue and all light blue squares to gray. Everything else keep the same as input.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...change all gray squares to pink and all light blue squares to gray. Everything else keep the same as input.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...change all brown squares to light blue and all light blue squares to brown. Everything else keep the same as input.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...outline the boxes with green, then fill in the boxes with black.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...fill in the holes of the circles with green, then black out the outlines of the circles.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...fill in the holes of the boxes with green, then blue out the outlines of the boxes.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...fill in the holes of the boxes with pink, then black out the outlines of the boxes.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...fill in the holes of the boxes with green, then black out the outlines of the boxes.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...cover the entire output grid with colored input grid blocks so there is a vertical line of colored blocks.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...color the whole output grid the color of the colored input grid blocks so there is a horizontal line of colored blocks.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...layer the whole output panel with the colored input grid blocks so that there is a diagonal line of colored blocks.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...fill the entire output grid with colored blocks to create vertical line of colored blocks.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...paint the entire output grid with the color of the colored input grid blocks so there is a circular line of colored blocks.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...clone and shift the full frame. In the end, all most of the central boxes will be brown. Look at the center of the grid; if there are boxes the same color as those in center, move it center to touch the center and then color light blue any boxes of same color that are left in the middle. Next, look at the top side of the grid, if there are any boxes the same color as the top side, move it center to touch the top side and then color light blue any boxes of same color that are left in the middle. Repeat these steps for the bottom and left side of the grid.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...paint and drop the entire canvas. In the end, none of the center boxes will be yellow. Look at the bottom of the grid; if there are boxes the same color as those on bottom, move it down to touch the bottom and then color blue any boxes of same color that are left in the middle. Next, look at the left side of the grid, if there are any boxes the same color as the left side, move it down to touch the left side and then color blue any boxes of same color that are left in the middle. Repeat these steps for the top and right side of the grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...copy and paste the entire box. In the end, almost all of the center boxes will be black. Look at the top of the grid; if there are boxes the same color as those on top, move it up to touch the top and then color black any boxes of same color that are left in the middle. Next, look at the right side of the grid, if there are any boxes the same color as the right side, move it up to touch the right side and then color black any boxes of same color that are left in the middle. Repeat these steps for the bottom and left side of the grid.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...duplicate and insert the whole block. In the end, some of the center boxes will be red. Look at the left of the grid; if there are boxes the same color as those on left, move it left to touch the left and then color green any boxes of same color that are left in the middle. Next, look at the top side of the grid, if there are any boxes the same color as the top side, move it left to touch the top side and then color green any boxes of same color that are left in the middle. Repeat these steps for the right and bottom side of the grid.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...mirror and shift the complete square. In the end, a few of the center boxes will be pink. Look at the right of the grid; if there are boxes the same color as those on right, move it right to touch the right and then color gray any boxes of same color that are left in the middle. Next, look at the bottom side of the grid, if there are any boxes the same color as the bottom side, move it right to touch the bottom side and then color gray any boxes of same color that are left in the middle. Repeat these steps for the top and left side of the grid.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...clone the input grid and detach the two shapes using the green grid. It has to be smaller than the size of the large input shape.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid and connect the two shapes with the blue grid.it must be smaller than the size of the small input shape.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid and connect the two shapes with the red grid. It must be larger than the size of the small input shape.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...replace the input grid and connect the two shapes using the yellow grid. It needs to be bigger than the size of the small input shape.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...replicate the input grid and disconnect the two shapes using the blue grid. It should be equal to the size of the small input shape.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...replace 3x3 same grid color with all other four different colors that in input grid. each 3x3 grid color are same in output grid 3x3.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...replace 2x2 same grid color with all other four different colors that in input grid. each 2x2 grid color are different in output grid 2x2.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...replace 2x2 same grid color with all other three different colors that in input grid. each 2x2 grid color are different in output grid 2x2.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...replace 2x3 same grid color with all other four different colors that in input grid. each 2x3 grid color are different in output grid 2x3.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...keep 2x2 same grid color with all other four different colors that in input grid. each 2x2 grid color are different in output grid 2x2.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...interrupt the repeating pattern consistently to the right end.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...break up the repeating pattern intermittently to the left end.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...disconnect the repeating pattern continuously to the far end.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...connect the varying pattern momentarily to the left end.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...connect the repeating pattern continuously to the right end.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...just fill the empty areas with pixels. Wherever a yellow and pink pixel touch on their sides (not corners), keep the yellow pixel and replace the pink one with gray.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...just replace the entire screen with green pixels. Wherever a green and green pixel touch on their sides, keep the green pixel and replace the other green one with red.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...copy the exact entire image. Where ever a green and red pixel touch on their sides (not diagonal/corners), replace the green pixel with light blue, and replace the red pixel with black. (remove it)
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...copy invertly the entire image. Wherever a blue and gray pixel touch on their sides (not diagonally), replace the blue pixel with pink and leave the gray pixel unchanged.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...draw a new image without touching the green and red pixels on their sides. Wherever a black and light blue pixel meet (not diagonally), keep the black pixel and replace the light blue one with green.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...extend each green dot straight up so it forms a vertical line. The green pixel must change direction as it reaches the pink pixel to the right and continue straight up.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...extend each grey dot straight up so it forms a vertical line. The grey pixel must change direction as it reaches the red pixel to the right and continue straight up.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...extend each blue dot straight up so it forms a vertical line. The blue pixel must change direction as it reaches the black pixel to the right and continue straight up.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...extend each red dot straight up so it forms a vertical line. The red pixel must change direction as it reaches the grey pixel to the right and continue straight up.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...extend each yellow dot straight up so it forms a vertical line. The yellow pixel must change direction as it reaches the brown pixel to the right and continue straight up.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...zoom into the different colored center block from the input grid and make every block colored.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...zoom out of the different colored center block from the input grid and make it the only colored block.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...zoom into the different colored center block from the input grid and make it the only colored block.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...zoom into the similarly colored corner block from the input grid and make it the only colored block.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...zoom into the different colored center block from the input grid and make it the only black block.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...copy and paste the left-side of the input (the yellow side) onto the output grid. Then, draw the green pattern on the output grid on top of the yellow (do not copy and paste because the black will overwrite the yellow). Your output grid should now have green and yellow on a black background. Then, recolor each green and yellow square pink, so your output is only pink and black.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...copy and paste the left-side of the input (the red side) onto the output grid. Then, draw the blue pattern on the output grid on top of the red (do not copy and paste because the green will overwrite the red). Your output grid should now have blue and red on a green background. Then, recolor each blue and red square grey, so your output is only grey and green.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...copy and paste the right-side of the input (the blue side) onto the output grid. Then, trace over the pink pattern on the output grid on top of the blue (do not copy and paste because the brown will overwrite the blue). Your output grid should now have pink and blue on a brown background. Then, recolor each pink and blue square green, so your output is only green and brown.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...copy and paste the right-side of the input (the light blue side) onto the output grid. Then, draw the grey pattern on the output grid on top of the light blue (do not copy and paste because the black will overwrite the light blue). Your output grid should now have grey and light blue on a black background. Then, recolor each grey and light blue square black, so your output is only black.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...move and paste the left-side of the input (the grey side) onto the output grid. Then, draw the red pattern on the output grid on top of the grey (do not move and paste because the yellow will overwrite the grey). Your output grid should now have red and grey on a yellow background. Then, recolor each red and grey square light blue, so your output is only light blue and yellow.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...clone the input. Start from the center, changing colors between brown and red, and decreasing the line by two blocks. So the colors should be brown in middle, then red, then brown, then red.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...mirror the input. Start from each side, switching colors from green to black, and decreasing the line by three blocks. So the color should be green in the middle, then black, then green, then black.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...duplicate the input. Start from each side, changing colors between pink and light green, and increasing the line by one block. So the colors should be pink in middle, then light green, then pink, then light green.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...reverse the input. Start from the corners, alternate colors between yellow and gray, and increasing the line by one block. So the colors should be yellow in the middle, then gray, then yellow, then gray.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...copy-paste the input. starting on each side, alternate colors between orange and light blue, and decreasing the line by one block. So the colors should be orange in middle, then light blue, then orange, then light blue.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...put a blue border around each yellow square. The thickness of the blue border should equal one half of the thickness of the yellow square (if the square is 6 squares across then the blue border should be three squares deep around it). Fill the black squares below the yellow and blue squares with a vertical line of gray squares. The gray squares should be in the same vertical row as the yellow square and should be the same width as the yellow square. If the gray line should intersect with a blue box, then the blue box should stay. Don't color over any blue.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...put a red border around each black square. The thickness of the red border should equal one half of the thickness of the black square (if the square is 6 squares across then the red border should be three squares deep around it). Fill the black squares below the black and red squares with a vertical line of green squares. The green squares should be in the same vertical row as the black square and should be the same width as the black square. If the green line should intersect with a red box, then the red box should stay. Don't color over any red.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...put a black border around each brown square. The thickness of the black border should equal one half of the thickness of the brown square (if the square is 6 squares across then the black border should be three squares deep around it). Fill the black squares below the brown and black squares with a vertical line of pink squares. The pink squares should be in the same vertical row as the brown square and should be the same width as the brown square. If the pink line should intersect with a black box, then the black box should stay. Don't color over any black.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...put a green border around each red square. The thickness of the green border should equal one half of the thickness of the red square (if the square is 6 squares across then the green border should be three squares deep around it). Fill the black squares below the red and green squares with a vertical line of blue squares. The blue squares should be in the same vertical row as the red square and should be the same width as the red square. If the blue line should intersect with a green box, then the green box should stay. Don't color over any green.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...put a yellow border around each blue square. The thickness of the yellow border should equal one half of the thickness of the blue square (if the square is 6 squares across then the yellow border should be three squares deep around it). Fill the black squares below the blue and yellow squares with a vertical line of red squares. The red squares should be in the same vertical row as the blue square and should be the same width as the blue square. If the red line should intersect with a yellow box, then the yellow box should stay. Don't color over any yellow.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...check the red grid which is at the same row and same line. draw a connected gray grid between the blue grid at the same row and line.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to... check the yellow grid which is at the same column and same line. draw a connected green grid between the blue grid at the same column and line.

shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...check the blue grid which is at the same row and same line. draw a connected light blue grid between the blue grid at the same row and line.

shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...identify the linear symmetry pattern in the input grid, and appropriately fill in the regions obscured by the green square to complete the linear symmetry pattern. Only represent the green square portion in the output grid.
