shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...identify the radial asymmetry pattern in the input grid, and appropriately fill in the regions obscured by the green square to complete the radial asymmetry pattern. Only represent the green square portion in the output grid.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...identify the radial symmetry pattern in the input grid, and appropriately leave the regions obscured by the green square to complete the radial symmetry pattern. Only represent the green square portion in the output grid.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...surround only the red squares with a blue border that is two squares wide.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...surround only the red squares with a pink border that is one square wide.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...surround only the green squares with a blue border that is one square wide.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...surround only the blue squares with a red border that is one square wide.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...surround only the red squares with a blue border that is one square wide.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...move the green rectangle one block closer to the yellow rectangle, no matter if it is horizontal, diagonal, or vertical.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...move the green square one block closer to the yellow square, no matter if it is horizontal, diagonal, or vertical.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...move the yellow square two blocks closer to the green square, no matter if it is horizontal, diagonal, or vertical.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...move the pink square one block further from the light blue square, no matter if it is horizontal, diagonal, or vertical.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...move the brown square three blocks closer to the red square, no matter if it is horizontal, diagonal, or vertical.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...fill the gray area with the colors corresponding with the numbered block in the first row.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...fill the gray area with the colors corresponding with the colored block in the first row.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...fill the black area with the colors corresponding with the colored block in the first row.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...fill the gray area with the colors corresponding with the colored block in the last row.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...leave the gray area blank and only fill in colored squares in the first row.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...look for the colored grid with the largest number of empty squares and use that color.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...look for the colored grid with the largest number of colored squares and use that color.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...look for the colored grid with the least color difference and use that color.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...look for the colored grid with the largest number of colored circles and use that color.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...look for the colored grid with the smallest number of colored squares and use that color.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...connect the black boxes that are directly vertical and horizontal to each other.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...disconnect the magenta boxes that are directly vertical and horizontal to each other.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...connect the light blue boxes that are directly vertical and horizontal to each other.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...connect the red boxes that are directly vertical and horizontal to each other.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...connect the magenta boxes that are diagonally to each other.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...add the same color blue pixel in a zig-zag pattern moving up the grid. Each pixel should be filled in on a diagonal going up and to the right until you read the edge of the grid. Then you should keep moving on the diagonal up and to the left until you reach the left side of the grid. Keep repeating until you reach the top of the grid. Then fill in the rest of the spaces with the light blue color.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...add the same color red pixel in a zig-zag pattern moving up the grid. Each pixel should be filled in on a diagonal going up and to the right until you reach the edge of the grid. Then you should keep moving on the diagonal up and to the left until you reach the left side of the grid. Keep repeating until you reach the top of the grid. Then fill in the rest of the spaces with the yellow color.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...add the same color green pixel in a zig-zag pattern moving up the grid. Each pixel should be filled in on a diagonal going up and to the right until you read the edge of the grid. Then you should keep moving on the diagonal up and to the left until you reach the left side of the grid. Keep repeating until you reach the top of the grid. Then fill in the rest of the spaces with the brown color.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...add the same color blue pixel in a zig-zag pattern moving down the grid. Each pixel should be filled in on a diagonal going down to the right until you reach the edge of the grid. Then you should keep moving the diagonal down to the left until you reach the left side of the grid. Keep repeating until you reach the bottom of the grid. Then fill in the rest of the spaces with the green color.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...add the same color blue pixel in a straight line pattern moving up the grid. Each pixel should be filled in vertically until you reach the top of the grid. Then fill in the rest of the spaces with the light blue color.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...break the lines at the edges, using alternating the color pattern.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...continue the lines to all edges, using alternating the color pattern.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...continue the lines to all corners, using alternating the color pattern.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...continue the lines to all edges, using the same color pattern.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...stop the lines before the edges, using alternating the color pattern.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...eliminate all the random color squares and replace them with the color of the circle they are in.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...eliminate all the random color squares and replace them with the color of the bar they are in.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...distribute all the random color squares and replace them with the color of the grid they are in.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...add some random color squares and replace them with the color of the bar they are in.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...distribute all the random color squares and replace them with the light of the bar they are in.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...fill in the blocks as if you have flipped the top side directly over the bottom side, taking the gray line out. The blocks directly below the gray line will overlap.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...fill in the blocks as if you have rotated the grid 180 degrees around the gray line. The blocks directly beside of the gray line will appear twisted.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...fill in the blocks as if you have folded the right side directly over the left side, taking the gray line out.. The blocks directly beside of the gray line will overlap.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...fill in the blocks as if you have folded the left side directly over the right side, taking the gray line out. The blocks directly beside of the gray line will overlap.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...fill in the blocks as if you have mirrored the grid along the gray line. The blocks directly beside of the gray line will look inverted.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...move the outside colors to the opposite sides, and make a square patterns with it. Rotate the inside shape counterclockwise 90 degree, 180 degree, 270 degree, and fill in all of these at once on the grid.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...transfer the outside color to the surrounding areas, making circle patterns. Then, rotate the inside pattern 30 degrees, 120 degrees, 240 degrees, and fill in every space on the grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...copy the outside color to the opposite corners of each side of the inside shape to make a square pattern. Then for the inside shape you have to visualize the pattern clockwise 90 degree, 180 degree, 270 degree, and fill in the grid with all of these overlay on top of each other.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...copy the outside color to the same corners on each side of the inside shape, making a rectangle pattern. Then the pattern inside should be rotated 45 degrees, 120 degrees, 200 degrees, and fill in the grid with each of these overlays.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...place the exterior color on the opposite edges, then make a pie-shaped pattern. For the interior shape, you have to consider the pattern at 60 degree, 180 degree, 270 degree, and fill in the grid with all these overlays on top of each other.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...calculate the red grid and place the meeting point of the colored grid-down through with the same count.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...count the pink grid and place the meeting point of the colored grid-down through with the same count.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...count the grey grid and place the intersection point of the colored grid-right with the same count.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...count the grey grid and place the meeting point of the colored grid-down through with the same count.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...count the grey grid and then place the meeting point of the colored grid-up through with the same count.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...locate all the pink squares that coincide with the pattern of the gray squares, then switch the pink squares in every pattern to light blue.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...find any black squares that are in the same pattern as the red squares, then change the black squares in each pattern to red.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...find any blue squares that are in the same pattern as the red squares, then change the blue squares in each pattern to green.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...spot all the yellow squares that match the pattern of the blue squares, then alter the yellow squares in each pattern to pink.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...seek out any green squares that are in the same pattern as the yellow squares, then modify the green squares in each pattern to brown.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...change pattern color to red if the pattern only has four 90 degree edge, pink if it has five and green if it has six. also if its shape is a 10 it is yellow, a f it is brown and a O it is black.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...change pattern color to green if the pattern only has one 90 degree edge, yellow if it has two and orange if it has three. also if it shape is a 200 it is blue, a d it is light blue and an N it is red.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...change pattern color to brown if the pattern only has one 30 degree edge, gray if it has two and black if it has three. also if it shape is a 3 it is gray, a e it is brown and an M it is pink.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...change pattern color to blue if the pattern only has one 90 degree edge, pink if it has two and red if it has three. also if it shape is a 1 it is red, a c it is pink and an L it is blue.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...change pattern color to blue if the pattern only has one 20 degree edge, pink if it has two and red if it has five. also if it shape is a 2 it is orange, a b it is yellow and an I it is green.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...copy the rectangular shape with the most red squares exactly.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...replicate the rectangular shape with the least blue squares exactly.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...copy the rectangular shape with the most yellow squares precisely.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...mimic the square shape with the most red pixels exactly.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...copy the square form with the most red rectangles accurately.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to... keep the output grid with no changes. Next place two different boxes on the grid where the interior colored boxes match.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...change the output grid to a different background color that does not include the two colored boxes. Next place the colored boxes on the grid where the interior colored boxes do not match.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...change the output grid to the same colored boxes that does not include the two boxes. Next place the boxes on the background color where the interior colored boxes match.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...change the output grid to the background color that does not include the two boxes. Next place the colored boxes on the grid where the interior colored boxes match.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...change the output grid to the background color that includes the two boxes. Next place the colored boxes on the grid where the interior colored boxes match.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...fill the edges with yellow.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...fill the nodes with black.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...fill the nodes with yellow.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...leave the nodes with yellow.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...empty the nodes with yellow.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...transfer the color pattern into the other blue grids.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...paste the color pattern into the other black grids.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...erase the color pattern from the other gray grids.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...remove the color pattern from the other gray grids.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...copy the color pattern into the other gray grids.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...change the single green pixels to black, two green pixel lines to brown, and three green pixel shapes to pink. The background stays yellow.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...change the single yellow pixels to blue, two yellow pixel lines to green, and three yellow pixel shapes to purple. The background stays black.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...change the single green pixels to black, two brown pixel lines to red, and three pink pixel shapes to purple. The background stays yellow.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...change the single black pixels to green, two black pixel lines to red, and three black pixel shapes to blue. The background stays gray.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...change the single gray pixels to purple, two gray pixel lines to red, and three gray pixel shapes to yellow. The background stays white.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...keep the colors of the patterns, shapes, size and the background as they are, copy the pattern on the yellow and pink colored grids, to the other grid which is not patterned hence retaining the pattern and size of the green grid, keep on adding new patterns vertically towards the only edge of the grid.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...without exchanging the colors of any patterns, shapes, size and the background, copy the pattern on the brown and gray colored grids, to the other grid which is not patterned hence making a distinct pattern and size from the blue grid, continue to add various patterns diagonally towards the only edge of the grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...alter the colors of the patterns, shapes, size and the background, copy the pattern on the black colored grids, to the other grid which is not patterned thus replicating it with the pattern and size of the black grid, continue to add the same pattern diagonally towards the only edge of the grid.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...without any change in the colors of any patterns, shapes, size and the background, copy the pattern on the black colored grids, to the other grid which is not patterned thus replicating it with the pattern and size of the black grid, continue to add the same pattern diagonally towards the only edge of the grid.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...without any change in the colors of any patterns, shapes, size and the background, copy the pattern on the green colored grids, to the other grid which is not patterned thus maintaining the same pattern and size of the blue grid, keep on adding different patterns vertically towards the opposite edge of the grid.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...add a 3x3 green cross between the two squares perfect.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...add a 2x2 green cross between the two squares perfect.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...add a 3x3 red cross between the two squares perfect.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...add a 3x3 green square between the two squares perfect.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...add a 3x3 green cross between the three squares perfect.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...split both patterns from above and below the yellow line.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...blend together the patterns to the left and right of the blue line.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...mesh apart the patterns from above and below the brown line.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...separate both patterns from above and below the gray line.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...mesh together both patterns from above and below the gray line.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to... start with the color that is on the left. Fill in that line with that color every other square, beginning with the first square. Fill in the rest in that line with the sixth color. For the next line, start with the color that is already there (the sixth color) and fill in in the same every other square pattern. It should look like a game board. The first color in every line is the color of the input grid.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...start with the color that is on the bottom. Fill in that line with that color every other square, begin with the first square. Fill in the rest in that line with the third color. For the next line, start with the color that is already there (the third color) and fill in in the same every other square pattern. It should look like an abstract painting. The first color in every line is the color of the input grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to... start with the color that is on the bottom right corner. Fill in the diagonals with that color every other square, begin with the first square. Fill in the rest of the diagonals with the fifth color. For the next diagonal, start with the color that is already there (the fifth color) and fill in the same every other square pattern. The output should resemble a diagonal checkerboard pattern. The first color in every diagonal is the color of the input grid.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...start with the color that is on the top. Fill in that line with that color every other square, begin with first square. Fill in the rest in that line with the second color. For the next line, start with the color that is already there (the second color) and fill in in the same every other square pattern. It should look like a game board. The first color in every line is the color of the input grid
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to... start with the color that is on the right. Fill in that column with that color every other square, begin with the first square. Fill in the rest in that column with the fourth color. For the next column, start with the color that was previously filled (the fourth color) and fill in in the same every other square pattern. It should look like a quilt pattern. The first color in every column is the color of the input grid.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...change the color of the lines. The longest line needs to be colored brown. The middle length line needs to be colored pink. The shortest line needs to be colored gray.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...maintain the color of the lines. The longest line needs to be colored red. The middle length line needs to be colored yellow. The shortest line needs to be colored blue.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...change the color of the lines. The shortest line needs to be colored blue. The middle length line needs to be colored yellow. The longest line needs to be colored red.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...change the color of the squares. The biggest square needs to be colored blue. The middle size square needs to be colored yellow. The smallest square needs to be colored red.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...change the color of the lines. The longest line needs to be colored blue. The middle length line needs to be colored yellow. The shortest line needs to be colored red.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...create an X by filling in the vertical tiles until the middle of each corner is reached.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...create a Z by filling in the diagonal tiles until the edge of each corner is reached.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...create an X by filling in the diagonal tiles until the edge of each corner is reached.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...create an X by filling in the horizontal tiles until the edge of each corner is reached.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...create a triangle by filling in the diagonal tiles until the edge of each corner is reached.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...remove the grid. Then paste the augmented pattern onto the output grid. Next, create a mirror pattern from the modified pattern underneath the existing pattern. Then transfer the whole modernized and mirrored arrangement to fill in the rest of the white grid.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...destroy the grid. Then copy the normal pattern onto the output grid. Afterwards, create a mirror pattern from the complex pattern next to the primitive pattern. Then move the whole refined and mirror pattern to fill in the rest of the blue grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...clear the grid. Then duplicate the simple pattern onto the output grid. Later, develop a mirror pattern from the irregular pattern beside the normal pattern. Then copy the whole unsophisticated and mirrored pattern to fill in the rest of the yellow grid.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...write on the grid. Then replicate the irregular pattern onto the output grid. Next, create a mirror pattern from the ordinary pattern above the unique pattern. Then paste the whole basic and reflected pattern to fill in the rest of the green grid.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...create the grid. Then copy the original pattern onto the output grid. Next, create a mirror pattern from the original pattern underneath the original pattern. Then copy the whole original and mirror pattern to fill in the rest of the black grid.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...put center box color in 1x1, outside box color in 3x3, then 5x5, then 7x7 and so on.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...put outside box color in 1x1, center box color in 3x3, then 5x5, then 7x7 and so on.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...put center box color in 7x7, outside box color in 3x3, then 5x5, then 1x1 and so on.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...put center box color in 1x1, outside box color in 5x5, then 3x3, then 7x7 and so on.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...put center box color in 3x3, outside box color in 1x1, then 7x7, then 5x5 and so on.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...shift horizontal lines from each corner of the outer squares towards the edge of the output grid.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...remove vertical lines from each corner of the outer squares towards the center of the output grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...add diagonal lines extending from each corner of the outer squares to the edge of the output grid.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...add diagonal lines extending from each corner of the outer circles to the edge of the output grid.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...add diagonal lines extending from each corner of the inner squares towards the edge of the output grid.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...illustrate the input grid. Draw cross lines from y color dots till it reaches the immediate lines of x color. The touch point should be painted with the y color. If the y color dot is between y color lines, make a horizontal line of y color passing through the y color dot and connecting the x color lines. keep a boundary around every y color dot (touch point) on the x color line with an x color triangle. It needs to be a triangle of x color with its tip of y color on the x color line. Done.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...mark the input grid. Create parallel lines from the dots of y color to touch the nearest squares of x color. The point of touch should be the y color. If the dot of y color is between 2 lines of y color you should make one lines of y color bypassing the dot of y color and bypassing the lines of x colors. Encircle each dot of y color (point of touch) on the line of x color with a circle of x color. It should be a square of x color with the center of x color on the line of x color. Done.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...duplicate the given grid. Draw intersecting lines from the squares of y color to get closer to the nearby lines of x color. The touching point has to be the y color. If the y color square is in between two y color lines, create a line of y color passing through the y color square and intersecting the lines of x colors. Surround the y color square (point of touch) where the x color line is with a rectangle of x color. it has to be a rectangle of x color with the core of y color on the x color line. Done.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid. Make perpendicular lines from the dots of y color to touch the closest lines of x color. The point of touch should be the y color. If the dot of y color is between 2 lines of y color you should make one lines of y color going through the dot of y color and connecting the lines of x colors. Surround each dot of y color (point of touch) on the line of x color with a square of x color. It should be a square of x color with the center of y color on the line of x color. Done.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...copy the input template. Draw diagonal lines from the dots of y color touching the immediate near lines of x color. The touching area needs to be of y color. In case the y color dot is between two lines of same color, construct a single y color line crossing the y color dot and linking the x color lines. Border every y color dot (point of contact) on the x color line with a polygon of x color. It should form a polygon of x color with the centre point of y color on the x color line. Done.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...flip the pattern in the input grid horizontally.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...rotate the pattern in the input grid 180 degrees.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...turn the pattern in the input grid counter-clockwise.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...turn the pattern in the input grid clockwise.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...flip the pattern in the input grid vertically.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...put brown squares in between the space that the red squares across from each other only left to right squares.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...put brown squares above the space that the red squares across from each other only left to right squares.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...put brown circles in between the space that the red squares across from each other only left to right squares.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...put green squares in between the space that the red squares across from each other only left to right squares.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...pull brown squares in between the space that the red squares across from each other only left to right squares.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid and flip it vertically. The green squares act as a starting point for you to draw lines, so if the green squares are on the left, you have to draw lines horizontally to the right and if the green squares are at the top, you have to draw the line vertically down. The red squares are to be avoided.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid and leave it as it is. The blue squares act as a starting point for you to draw lines, so if the blue squares are on the left, you have to draw lines horizontally to the right and if the blue squares are at the top, you have to draw the line vertically down. Next, after copying the grid, draw lines from each blue squares and stop just before the grid with the first red square. Then you will start again to draw your second blue lines starting from the grid with the red square, however, you will have to move your line by one grid according to the position of your red square - if your red square is at the bottom, you will move the second line up by one grid, if your red square is at the right, you will have to move your second line left by one grid and if your red square is at the left, you will have to move your second line to the right by one grid. These second blue lines stop just before the grid with the second red square. You will then draw another set of blue lines with the same rule as the second line all the way to the end of the grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...clear the input grid and start anew. The black squares are a starting point for you to draw lines in a spiral, clockwise pattern. The red squares are to be completely ignored.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...alter the input grid heavily. The red squares act as a starting point for you to draw lines, so if the red squares are on the left, you have to draw lines horizontally to the right and if the red squares are at the top, you have to draw the line vertically down. Avoid all the blue squares when drawing.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...replace all the squares in the input grid with yellow squares. No lines are to be drawn; the grid should be completely uniform and consist solely of yellow squares. No attention should be paid to the blue or red squares in the input.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...bring the indistinguishable colored block, pull it inside from the frame and stop the single line to edge. fill in frame without color of frame.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...leave the outstanding colored pixel, move it into the middle of the frame and follow the triple line to edge. empty the frame with color of frame.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...take the outstanding colored block, leave it in the frame and interrupt the continuous line to edge. empty the frame with color of frame.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...move the least noticeable colored block, pull it back into the frame and continue the double line to edge. fill in frame with color of frame.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...take the outstanding colored block, move it to outside the frame and continue the single line to edge. fill in frame with color of frame.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...triple pattern and fit the resulting pattern to scale. If it's 1x5 the result should be 3x15.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...double the pattern, but keep the same scale. If it's 1x5 the result should be 2x5.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...halve the pattern and fit the resulting pattern to scale. If it's 1x5 the result should be 0.5x2.5.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...double pattern and fit the resulting pattern to scale. If it's 1x5 the result should be 2x10.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...reduce the pattern and fit the resulting pattern to scale. If it's 1x5 the result should be 0.5x2.5.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...reflect the pattern upside down like it was up against a mirror.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...shift the pattern downwards like it was falling off a cliff.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...rotate the pattern counter-clockwise like it was up against a windmill.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...reflect the pattern left to right like it was looking into a mirror.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...rotate the pattern clockwise like it was up against a fan.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...combine the orange and grey into one pattern that take up a 3x4 space. Fill each black space with red. Fill the old pattern with white. You should only have blue spaces.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...combine the orange and grey into one pattern that take up a 3x4 space. Fill each white space with green. Fill the old pattern with black. You should only have orange spaces.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...combine the orange and grey into one pattern that take up a 4x3 space. Fill each black space with green. Fill the old pattern with black. You should only have green spaces.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...combine the green and black into one pattern that take up a 4x3 space. Fill each white space with blue. Fill the old pattern with purple. You should only have red spaces.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...combine the red and blue into one pattern that take up a 4x3 space. Fill each yellow space with grey. Fill the old pattern with orange. You should only have brown spaces.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...mimic the output grid, determine the shades of the colored squares. We can refer to them as shade E and shade F. Around the squares with shade E, produce a 2x2 square of shade F, covering the shade E squares. Around the squares with shade F, yield a 2x2 square of shade E, covering the shade F squares. Now we will have three 2x2 squares, where two squares are of shade E with a square of shade F in their centers.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...duplicate the input grid, recognize the colors of the colored squares. They will be known as color I and color J. Around the squares with color I, construct a 3x3 triangle with color J, containing the color I squares. Around the squares with color J, create a 3x3 triangle with color I, containing the color J squares. Now we will have four 3x3 triangles, where two triangles are of color I with a square of color J in their centers.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...take the input grid, recognize the colors of the colored squares. We will name them color C and color D. Around the squares with color C, form a 4x4 square with color D, enclosing the color C squares. Around the squares with color D, form a 4x4 square with color C, enclosing the color D squares. Now we should have four 4x4 squares, in which two squares are color C with D colored square right at their center.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...recreate the output grid, identify the hues of the colored squares. Let us denote them as hue G and hue H. Around the squares with hue G, form a 3x3 rectangle with hue H, surrounding the hue G squares. Around the squares with hue H, form a 3x3 rectangle with hue G, surrounding the hue H squares. Now we will have five 3x3 rectangles, in which two rectangles are of hue G with a square of hue H in their centers.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid, identify the colors of the colored grids. we will call it color A and color B. Around the grids with color A, create a 3x3 square with color B, surrounding the color A grids. Around the grids with color B, create a 3x3 square with color A, surrounding the color B grids. Now we should have four 3x3 squares, in which two squares are A color with B colored grid in their centers.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...use the input grid as 4 sections of the output so that there is a pattern of the first colored circles, then using light blue make lines up and down from the colored squares to until you reach another colored square or the end of the output grid.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...use the input grid as 4 sections of the output so that there is a pattern of the first colored squares, then using light blue make lines sideways from the colored squares until you reach another colored square or the end of the output grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...use the input grid as 4 sections of the output so that there is a pattern of the first colored squares, then using green make lines up and down from the colored squares until you reach another colored square or the end of the output grid.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...use the in put grid as 4 sections of the out put so that there is a pattern of the first colored squares, then using light blue make lines up and down from the colored squares to until you reach another colored square or the end of the out put grid.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...use the input grid as 2 sections of the output so that there is a pattern of the first colored squares, then using light blue make lines up and down from the colored squares until you reach another colored square or the end of the output grid.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...replace the grey boxes with the color and replace the black boxes with color.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...replace the color boxes with the grey and replace the black boxes with color.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...replace the grey boxes with the color and replace the color boxes with black.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...replace the black boxes with the grey and replace the color boxes with grey.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...replace the grey boxes with black and replace the color boxes with grey.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...flip the blue pattern over the red one like a mirror image. The resulting output should now have the grey pattern outside of the orange one.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...flip the orange pattern over the red one like an mirror image. The resulting output should now have the grey pattern outside of the orange one.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...flip the grey pattern over the red one like an mirror image. The resulting output should now have the grey pattern outside of the orange one.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...flip the grey pattern over the yellow one like a mirror image. The resulting output should now have the grey pattern outside of the yellow one.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...flip the grey pattern over the green one like a mirror image. The resulting output should now have the green pattern outside of the orange one.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...order the color boxes. avoid a large number of the color box.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...scramble the color boxes. Include a large number of the color box.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...disorder the color boxes. Pick a large number of the color box.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...shuffle the color boxes. Favour a maximum quantity of the color box.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...randomize the color boxes. Use a minimal amount of the color box.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...change the background color from black to light gray, then continue the pattern of lines, with the same spacing and bends.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...change the background color from black to light pink, then continue the pattern of lines, without any spacing or bends.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...leave the background color as black, then continue the pattern of lines, with the same spacing and bends.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...change the background color from blue to light blue, then continue the pattern of lines, with the same spacing and bends.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...change the background color from black to light brown, then stop the pattern of lines, with different spacing and bends.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...count the number of pixels composing the objects in the input grid. In the output grid, fill the color of the object with the highest pixel count, arranging it vertically as a 3x1 structure from top to bottom.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...count the number of pixels composing the objects in the input grid. In the output grid, fill the color of the object with the highest pixel count, arranging it horizontally as a 3x1 structure from left to right.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...count the number of pixels composing the objects in the input grid. In the output grid, fill the color of the object with the highest pixel count, arranging it horizontally as a 1x3 structure from top to bottom.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...count the number of pixels composing the objects in the input grid. In the output grid, fill the color of the object with the highest pixel count, arranging it vertically as a 1x3 structure from left to right.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...count the number of pixels composing the objects in the input grid. In the output grid, fill the color of the object with the lowest pixel count, arranging it vertically as a 3x1 structure from top to bottom.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...fill the black portion of the input circle to correspond to the overall pattern. In the output circle, only represent the filled black part from the input circle.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...fill the black portion of the input grid to correspond to the different pattern. In the output grid, only represent the filled black part from the input grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...fill the blue portion of the input grid to correspond to the overall pattern. In the output grid, only represent the filled blue part from the input grid.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...empty the black portion of the input grid to correspond to the overall pattern. In the output grid, only represent the filled black part from the input grid.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...fill the black portion of the input grid to correspond to the overall pattern. In the output grid, only represent the filled black part from the input grid.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...develop a 5x5 grid and flood fill it with red color. Next, replicate the gray pattern to the 5x5 grid. Then, overlay the yellow pattern atop of the gray pattern. After that, fill in the red squares with black color and fill in all the gray and yellow squares with red color.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...create a 3x3 grid and flood fill it with black color. Next, copy the brown pattern to the 3x3 grid. Then, overlap the blue pattern on top of the brown pattern. After that, fill in the black squares with red color and fill in all the brown and blue squares with black color.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...establish a 2x2 grid and flood fill it with blue color. Next, duplicate the pink pattern to the 2x2 grid. Then, meet the green pattern above the pink pattern. After that, fill in the blue squares with black color and fill in all pink and green squares with blue color.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...create a 3x3 grid and fill it with white color. Next, copy the white pattern to the 3x3 grid. Then, overlap the green pattern on top of the white pattern. After that, fill in the white squares with orange color and fill in all the green and red squares with white color.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...generate a 4x4 grid and flood fill it with light blue color. Next, copy the gray pattern to the 4x4 grid. Then, add the black pattern on top of the gray pattern. After that, fill in the light blue squares with blue color and fill in all the gray and black squares with light blue color.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...verify the exterior of empty hexagons to determine the number of single pixels within them. Duplicate the hexagon with the least single pixels, excluding the single pixels, to the output grid. Replace the colors of the hexagon to match the colors of the single pixels inside it.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...examine the exterior of filled squares to determine the number of duplicated pixels within them. Copy the square with the minimum duplicated pixels, including the duplicated pixels, to the output grid. Change the colors of the square to contrast the colors of the multi pixels inside it.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...inspect the interior of filled rectangles to ascertain the number of multiple pixels within them. Replicate the rectangle with the maximum multi pixels, excluding the multi pixels, into the output grid. Substitute the colors of the rectangle to complement the colors of the double pixels inside it.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...scrutinize the interior of empty circles to assess the number of triple pixels within them. Duplicate the circle with the least triple pixels, excluding the triple pixels, to the output grid. Replace the colors of the circle to match the colors of the single pixels inside it.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...check the interior of empty rectangles to determine the number of single pixels within them. Copy the rectangle with the most single pixels, including the single pixels, to the output grid. Replace the colors of the rectangle to match the colors of the single pixels inside it.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...reproduce the input grid directly into the output grid. Then, for each 2x2 square, tally the number of unique colors present. Append 1x1 orange pixels below that 2x2 square, identical to the amount of exclusive colors held within it.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...transcribe the input grid directly onto the output grid. Then, for each 3x3 square, check the number of unique colors present. Append 1x2 green pixels beneath that 3x3 square, equivalent to the number of distinct colors encapsulated within it.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...copy the input grid directly into the output grid. Then, for each 2x2 square, check the number of unique colors present. Append 1x2 green pixels below that 2x2 square, equal to the number of distinct colors contained within it.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...mirror the input grid precisely into the output grid. Then, for each 2x2 square, calculate the number of unique colors present. Append 1x3 blue pixels below that 2x2 square, corresponding to the number of individual colors enclosed within it.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...duplicatel the input grid exactly into the output grid. Then, for each 1x1 square, observe the count of unique colors present. Append 2x2 pink pixels below that 1x1 square, proportionate to the number of distinct colors contained within it.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...look at the number and positions of colored pixels in a 5x1 input grid. The output grid is a square with both its height and width equalling five times the number of colored pixels found in the input grid. Replicate the input grid to the bottom-left 5x1 area of the output grid, diverging from the existing colored pixels, stretch every pixel diagonally towards the top-right heading of the output grid until touching the edge.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...inspect the quantity and location of colored pixels in a 1x5 input grid. Place the input grid in the top-left 1x5 section of the output grid, proceeding from the original colored pixels, send each pixel diagonally in the bottom-right direction of the output grid till you reach the limit.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...examine the count and sites of colored pixels in a 1x5 input grid. Transfer input grid to the top-left 1x5 area of the output grid; starting from the current colored pixels, move each pixel diagonally towards the bottom-right of the output grid until the border is touched.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...check the number and positions of colored pixels in a 1x5 input grid. Copy input grid to the top-right 1x5 section of the output grid, then expanding from existing colored pixels, stretch each pixel diagonally towards the bottom-left direction of the output grid until hitting the border.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...check the number and positions of colored pixels in a 1x5 input grid. The output grid is a square with both its width and height equal to five times the number of colored pixels identified in the input grid. Copy the input grid to the bottom-left 1x5 section of the output grid, and starting from the existing colored pixels, extend each pixel diagonally towards the top-right direction of the output grid until reaching the border.

shuffled_description1: To make the output, you have to...check how many 2x2 red squares are present in the input grid. Then, fill the corresponding number of 1x1 blue pixels in a 3x3 black background output grid. When filling the blue pixels, follow the order: top-left corner, top-right corner, center, bottom-left corner, bottom-right corner.
shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...check how many 2x2 red squares are present in the input grid. Then, fill the corresponding number of 1x1 blue pixels in a 4x4 black background output grid. When filling the blue pixels, follow the order: top-left corner, top-right corner, center, bottom-left corner, bottom-right corner.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...check how many 2x2 red rectangles are present in the input grid. Then, fill the corresponding number of 1x1 blue circles in a 3x3 black background output grid. When filling the blue pixels, follow the order: top-left corner, top-right corner, center, bottom-left corner, bottom-right corner.
shuffled_description4: To make the output, you have to...check how many 2x2 blue squares are present in the input grid. Then, fill the corresponding number of 1x1 red pixels in a 3x3 black background output grid. When filling the red pixels, follow the order: top-left corner, top-right corner, center, bottom-left corner, bottom-right corner.
shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...check how many 3x3 red squares are present in the input grid. Then, fill the corresponding number of 1x1 blue pixels in a 3x3 black background output grid. When filling the blue pixels, follow the order: top-left corner, top-right corner, center, bottom-left corner, bottom-right corner.

shuffled_description2: To make the output, you have to...fill the blue rectangle with the same pattern with the input grid.
shuffled_description3: To make the output, you have to...fill the blue circle with the same pattern with the input grid.

shuffled_description5: To make the output, you have to...fill the blue square with the same pattern with the input grid.
